A message was sent to you regarding record request #26-245:

This response is to your request of May 9, Next Request #26-245.&nbsp;Pleas=
e see our responses below corresponding to your numbered requests.

&nbsp;

1. Authorization and Access Structure

This request does not seek the names, passwords, or login credentials of in=
dividual users. It seeks the following administrative governance records, n=
one of which create a security vulnerability and none of which are ALPR dat=
a:

The personnel classifications or job categories authorized to access and se=
arch the Flock Safety ALPR system, for example: sworn patrol deputy, detect=
ive, crime analyst, records personnel, or other designated role

Response:&nbsp;Please see Policy 433.2(b) and 433.3.1(a).&nbsp;

&nbsp;

The written process by which access to the Flock Safety system is granted t=
o an individual, including who approves access requests and what criteria m=
ust be met

Response:&nbsp;Please see Policy 433.2(b) and 433.3.1(a).

&nbsp;

The written process by which access to the Flock Safety system is revoked, =
including the circumstances triggering revocation and who is responsible fo=
r executing it

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

The training curriculum, course materials, or written training standards re=
quired to be completed before a member is authorized to access the ALPR sys=
tem, as referenced in Policy 433.3.1(b) and Policy 433.4(g)

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any training completion records, rosters, or certifications documenting whi=
ch personnel classifications have satisfied the training requirement during=
 the requested period, excluding individual names if YCSO contends those ar=
e exempt, but including aggregate counts by personnel classification, date =
range, and training module completed

Response:&nbsp;Subject to certain exceptions stated in Penal Code section 8=
32.7, the personnel records of peace officers and custodial officers and re=
cords maintained by a state or local agency pursuant to Section 832.5, or i=
nformation obtained from these records, are confidential and shall not be d=
isclosed in any criminal or civil proceeding except by discovery pursuant t=
o Sections 1043 and 1046 of the Evidence Code.&nbsp;(Penal Code =C2=A7832.7=
.)&nbsp;Therefore, to the extent such record may exist, it would be exempt =
from disclosure under the Public Records Act. (Govt. Code =C2=A77927.705.)

&nbsp;

2. Audit Log Integrity and Platform Transition Records

&nbsp;

The prior response indicated that no internal audit logs exist beyond the F=
lock Safety Transparency Portal. This category does not re-request the unde=
rlying log. It requests records bearing on the integrity and completeness o=
f whatever records do exist:

&nbsp;

Any records showing ALPR searches that were deleted, voided, modified, or o=
therwise removed from the active log after initial entry, including any cha=
nge log, edit history, or audit trail associated with search records

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any records documenting the December 2025 Flock Safety platform change, inc=
luding any communications between YCSO personnel and Flock Safety regarding=
 the effect of that change on officer-level free-text logging, reason field=
 documentation, or user attribution in search records

Response:&nbsp;Please see the agenda and material from the Board of Supervi=
sors meetings of August 26, 2025 (agenda item 415/2025), July 22, 2025 (age=
nda item 263/2025) available on the County website.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Any internal YCSO assessment, memorandum, or communication addressing wheth=
er the Flock Safety Transparency Portal satisfies YCSO's documentation obli=
gations under Civil Code =C2=A7 1798.90.52 and Policy 433.6(e)

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any records showing what officer-level search documentation, if any, YCSO m=
aintains independently of the Flock platform, including any locally stored =
logs, dispatch records, CAD entries, or other records that capture the reas=
on for an ALPR search at the individual officer level; or, if no such recor=
ds exist, a written statement to that effect

Response:&nbsp;This request is overly broad.&nbsp;In order for us to assist=
 you, we request that you provide the specific instance, report number, loc=
ation,&nbsp;date, and time for any CAD information you are requesting.&nbsp=
;&nbsp;

&nbsp;

3. Annual Audit Documentation =E2=80=94 Policy 433.8

&nbsp;

All internal memoranda, audit reports, compliance summaries, or any equival=
ent documentation produced pursuant to ALPR Policy 433.8, including:

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any memoranda from the Operations Division Captain or Sheriff's designee to=
 the Sheriff documenting ALPR usage audits for the requested period

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any substitute, equivalent, or alternative documentation that YCSO contends=
 satisfies the Policy 433.8 annual audit requirement

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

If no such records exist, a written statement confirming that no annual aud=
its were conducted or documented for the period covered by this request

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

4. Interagency Data Sharing =E2=80=94 Written Requests and Approvals

&nbsp;

Pursuant to ALPR Policy 433.9, which requires written requests and Sheriff =
or designee approval before ALPR data is shared with outside agencies, and =
requires approved requests to be retained on file:

&nbsp;

All written requests received from outside agencies for access to YCSO Floc=
k Safety ALPR data during the requested period

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

All written approvals or denials of such requests

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any internal YCSO records, directives, or written policies governing YCSO p=
ersonnel=E2=80=99s use of the State, Nationwide, Law Enforcement, or Commun=
ity Network access tiers to query plate data collected by agencies other th=
an YCSO, including any authorization or approval required before such acces=
s is used.

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

If no written requests, approvals, or denials exist for the requested perio=
d, a written statement confirming that no outside agency requested YCSO Flo=
ck data and that YCSO personnel did not access other agencies=E2=80=99 data=
 through the network tiers described above during the period covered by thi=
s request

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

5. SB 34 Compliance Documentation

&nbsp;

Any internal audits, compliance reviews, assessments, or correspondence add=
ressing YCSO=E2=80=99s compliance with Civil Code =C2=A7 1798.90.5 et seq. =
(SB 34), including:

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any communications between YCSO personnel and Flock Safety representatives =
regarding SB 34 compliance, documentation requirements, audit log completen=
ess, or platform changes affecting officer-level logging

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any communications between YCSO and the California Department of Justice re=
garding ALPR usage or SB 34 reporting obligations

Response: We have no documents responsive to this request.

&nbsp;

Any internal assessments of whether the Flock Safety Transparency Portal sa=
tisfies YCSO's SB 34 documentation requirements

Response:&nbsp;We have no documents responsive to this request.



&nbsp;

Please consider this as a final response to your Public Record Act Request.

&nbsp;



&nbsp;

If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact our office at (=
530) 749-7565.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

&nbsp;








